---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Is SO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)" description="SO is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's the fifth note of the musical scale (sol). Extensions include SOB, SOD, SON, SOP, SOT, SOW, SOX, SOY." keywords="is so a scrabble word, so scrabble, so valid scrabble, so points scrabble, two letter s words, so meaning scrabble, so extensions scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Is SO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)","description":"SO is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's the fifth note of the musical scale (sol).","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-so-a-scrabble-word"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is SO a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, SO is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) Scrabble dictionaries. It scores 2 points (S=1, O=1) and refers to the fifth note of the musical scale, a variant of 'sol.'"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What words can you extend SO into?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"SO extends into many useful words: SOB (5pts), SOD (4pts), SON (3pts), SOP (5pts), SOT (3pts), SOW (6pts), SOX (10pts), SOY (6pts). SOX is the highest-scoring extension at 10 points thanks to X(8)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is SO better to play than other 2-letter S words?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"SO scores only 2 points, same as most S+vowel combos. But its real value is the extensions — SOX (10pts), SOW (6pts), SOY (6pts) are excellent follow-up plays. SO is best used as a setup move rather than a final play."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is SO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Yes, SO is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's the fifth note of the musical scale (a variant spelling of "sol" from do-re-mi-fa-sol). While only 2 points on its own, SO is incredibly versatile — it extends into 8+ three-letter words, including SOX at 10 points.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ VALID</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">SO</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">2 points · S=1, O=1 · The fifth note of the musical scale (sol)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Valid in both TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words). SO is a musical term — the fifth note in the solfège system. Its real power lies in the massive number of 3-letter extensions available.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 S-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 O-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">SO Extensions: Where the Value Lives</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SOX</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SOW</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SOY</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SOB</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SOP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SOD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SON</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SOT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">SO Strategy: Setup Mastery</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Setup for SOX:</span> Play SO near an X-friendly position. Next turn, extend to SOX (10pts). S+O are both common tiles, making this setup easy to execute. SOX is one of the best 3-letter words in the game.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel play enabler:</span> S forms valid 2-letter words with nearly every letter (SH, SI, SO, etc). Play SO parallel to existing words — S will almost always form a valid crossword, giving you bonus points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Don't waste S on SO alone:</span> S is the most valuable tile for hooks (adding S to existing words). Use SO only when it creates crosswords or sets up extensions. Playing SO alone wastes your S tile's hooking potential.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Musical Notes in Scrabble</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">SO is part of the <span class="text-white font-medium">solfège musical scale</span> — do, re, mi, fa, sol, la, ti. Several of these are valid Scrabble words: DO (3pts), RE (2pts), MI (4pts), FA (5pts), SO (2pts), LA (2pts), TI (2pts). Memorize all seven for extra options.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ti-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is TI a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-ut-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is UT a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
